A <code>CloseEvent</code> is sent to clients using <a href="/en-US/docs/Glossary/WebSockets" class="glossaryLink" title="WebSockets: WebSocket is a protocol that allows for a persistent TCP connection between server and client so they can exchange data at any time.">WebSockets</a> when the connection is closed. This is delivered to the listener indicated by the <code>WebSocket</code> object's <code>onclose</code> attribute.